description: A small company manufactures customized bicycles. Whenever the sales department receives an order, a new process instance is created. If a member of the sales department rejects the order for a customized bike, the customer is informed. If a member of the sales department accepts the order for a customized bike, the storehouse and the engineering department are informed. Then the storehouse immediately processes the part list of the order. The storehouse checks the required quantity of each part. If the part is available, it is reserved. If the part is not available, it is back ordered. After the engineering department prepares everything for the assembling of the ordered bicycle, the engineering department assembles the bicycle. When the sales department ships the bicycle to the customer , the process instance finishes.

description: The process of an office supply request starts when any employee of the organization submits an office supply request. Next the requirement is registered. After that, the request is received by the immediate supervisor of the employee requesting the office supplies. Afterwards, the supervisor must assess the request. In case the request is asked to make a change, the request is closed. If the request is approved, it will go to the purchase department that will be in charge of selecting a vendor. If the vendor is not valid in the system, the purchase department will have to choose a different vendor. A vendor is selected and confirmed. Then the system will send a purchase order. After that, the system waits for the invoice to be received. In any case the system will send a notification to let the user know what the result was.

description: First an employee purchases a product or service that he requires. For instance, a sales person on a trip rents a car. Before a supervisor reviews the expense report, the employee submits an expense report with a list of items, along with the receipts for each item. Next she approves or rejects the report. This review could be automated, to reduce the workload on the supervisor. If the supervisor rejects the report, the employee, who submitted it, receives a response with reasons why the report was rejected. If the supervisor approves the report, the report is handed over to the treasurer. Afterwards, the treasurer checks the report. In case everything is in order, the treasurer accepts the expenses for processing. If receipts are missing or do not match the report, he makes the corrections himself . Then the process waits for the payment confirmation. After the payment is confirmed, the process ends.

description: Initially a staff meeting of the entire medical team is scheduled. The medical team consists of medical workers, physicians, and a psychiatrist. At this meeting, the team leader assigns all new patients on the list to members of the team. Each patient will be assigned to a social worker, who will act as the first intaker of the patient. One of the physicians will act as the second intaker. In assigning intakers, the teamleader takes into account their expertise as well as the region they are responsible for. Before the recording is handed to the secretarial office, the assignments are recorded on an assignment list . In case of a new assignment, it is also determined whether the medical file of the patient is required. After this information is added to the assignment list, the secretarial office stores the assignment of each patient of the assignment list in the information system. It passes the produced registration cards to the first and second intaker of each newly assigned patient. An intaker keeps this registration with him at times when visiting the patient and in his close proximity when he is at the office. For each patient for which the medical file is required, the secretarial office prepares a letter. Next, the secretarial office sends a letter to the family doctor of the patient. As soon as this copy is received. The secretarial office will inform the second intaker . Afterwards, the secretarial office will add the copy to the patient file . The first intaker plans a meeting with the patient as soon as this is possible. During the first meeting, the patient is examined using a standard checklist which is filled out. Then additional observations are registered in a personal notebook. After a visit, the first intaker puts a copy of these notes in the file of a patient. The standard checklist is also added to the file of the patient. The second intaker plans the first meeting . Physicians use dictaphones during meetings with patients. Once the secretarial office types out these tapes, the information is added to the patient file. Thereafter the secretarial office puts the patient on the list of patients. They provide the teamleader with a list of these patients. For each of these patients, the first and second intaker together formulate a treatment plan. This treatment plan formally ends the intake procedure.

description: First a request is received . The customer transmits his data to the customer service department. The customer service is a shared service center between the sales and distribution departments. Then the customer data is received by customer service. Then a customer data object is entered into the crm system. When the data object should be compared with the internal customer database, it should be checked for completeness and plausibility. If there are any errors, these should be corrected on the basis of a simple error list. The comparison of data is done to prevent individual customer data being stored multiple times. In case the customer does not exist in the customer data base, a new customer object is being created. This object consists of data elements such as the customers name and address and the assigned power gauge. The generated customer object is then used in combination with other data to prepare the contract documents . This includes data such as bank connections, information on the selected rate, requested date of switch-over. Afterwards, an automated check of the contract documents is carried out within the cis (customer information system) . In case of a negative response, i.e. the contract documents are not (or incorrectly) generated, the causing issues are identified. In the next step, the contract documents are generated once again. If a positive response is received , a confirmation document is sent out to the customer . Subsequently a request to the grid operator is automatically sent out by the cis. It puts the question whether the customer may be supplied by the selected supplier in the future. Before the grid operator transmits a response comment, the request is checked by the grid operator for supplier concurrence. Whenever there is supplier concurrence, the grid operator would inform all involved suppliers . Next the grid operator communicates with the old supplier. After that, the grid operator carries out the termination of the sales agreement between the customer and the old supplier. If there are not any objections by the grid operator (i.e. no supplier concurrence), the customer service creates a cis contract. The customer then has the chance to check the contract details. Based on this check he may decide to either withdraw from the switch contract or confirm it. . The process flow at customer service either ends (in case of withdrawal) or continues (in case of a confirmation). An additional constraint is that the customer can only withdraw from the offered contract within 7 days. The confirmation message by the customer is therefore not absolutely necessary . The confirmation message will count as accepted after 7 days in any way . The confirmation message can speed up the switch process. When the grid operator transmits the power meter data to the customer service and the old supplier, the grid operator computes the final billing based on the meter data. The grid operator sends the final billing to the old supplier. Likewise the old supplier creates and sends the final billing to the customer. For the customer as well as the grid operator the process ends then. After receiving the meter data . The customer service imports the meter data to systems that require the information. The process of winning a new customer ends here.

description: At the beginning the customer perceives that her subscribed service has degraded. A list with all the problem parameters is then sent to the customer service department of teleco. At the customer service an employee enters a problem report into the system based on the received data. Subsequently the problem report is compared to the customer sla to identify what the extent and the details of the service degradation are. Based on this, the necessary counter measures are determined including their respective priorities. An electronic service then determines the significance of the customer based on information that has been collected during the history of the contractual relationship. If it is a premium customer , the process will link to an extra problem fix process which will not be detailed here. If the customer is of certain significance which would affect the counter measures previously decided upon, the process goes back to reprioritize these measures. Taking together the information (i.e. contract commitment data + prioritized actions), a detailed problem report is created. Thereafter the detailed problem report is sent to service management. Service management deals on a first level with violations of quality in services that are provided to customers. After receiving the detailed problem report, service management investigates whether the problem is analyzable at the level of their department or not. If Service Management assesses the problem to be not analyzable by themselves, the detailed problem report is sent out to Resource Provisioning. Whenever Service Management is sure they can analyze it, they perform the analysis . Based on the outcome they create a trouble report that indicates the type of problem. Afterwards, resource provisioning receives the detailed problem report. Subsequently it is checked whether there are any possible problems. If resource provisioning does not find any problems, a notification about the normal service execution is created. Whenever a problem is detected , this will be analyzed by Resource Provisioning . In either case, a status report is created . Thereafter the status report is sent back to service management. Service management then prepares the final status report based on the received information. Subsequently it has to be determined what counter measures should be taken depending on the information in the final status report. Next two alternative process paths may be taken. For the case that no problem was detected at all, the actual service performance is sent back to the Customer Service. For the case that minor corrective actions are required, Service Management will undertake corrective actions by themselves. Before the problem resolution report is sent out to customer service, the problem resolution report is created. Subsequently this process path of service management ends.

description: At the beginning the customer perceives that her subscribed service has degraded. A list with all the problem parameters is then sent to the customer service department of teleco. At the customer service an employee enters a problem report into the system based on the received data. Next, the problem report is compared to the customer sla to identify what the extent and the details of the service degradation are. Based on this, the necessary counter measures are determined including their respective priorities. An electronic service then determines the significance of the customer based on information that has been collected during the history of the contractual relationship. If the customer is premium, the process will link to an extra problem fix process which will not be detailed here. If the customer is of certain significance which would affect the counter measures previously decided upon, the process goes back to reprioritize these measures. Taking together the information (i.e. contract commitment data + prioritized actions), a detailed problem report is created. Subsequently the detailed problem report is sent to service management. Service management deals on a first level with violations of quality in services that are provided to customers. After receiving the detailed problem report, service management investigates whether the problem is analyzable at the level of their department or not. If Service Management assesses the problem to be not analyzable by themselves, the detailed problem report is sent out to Resource Provisioning. If Service Management is sure they can analyze it, they perform the analysis . Based on the outcome they create a trouble report that indicates the type of problem. Next, resource provisioning receives the detailed problem report. Afterwards, it is checked whether there are any possible problems. If resource provisioning does not find any problems, a notification about the normal service execution is created. Whenever a problem is detected , this will be analyzed by Resource Provisioning . In either case, a status report is created . The status report is sent back to service management. Service management then prepares the final status report based on the received information. Afterwards, it has to be determined what counter measures should be taken depending on the information in the final status report. Next two alternative process paths may be taken. Whenever no problems were detected at all , the actual service performance is sent back to the Customer Service. For the case that minor corrective actions are required, Service Management will undertake corrective actions by themselves. When the problem resolution report is created, the problem resolution report is sent out to customer service. Next, the process path ends.

description: For the case that automatic resource restoration from resource provisioning is required, service management must create a request for automatic resource restoration. This message is then sent to resource provisioning. There is a deadline of 2 days. After the restoration request is received, all possible errors are tracked. Based on the tracked errors, all necessary corrective actions are undertaken by resource provisioning. In the next step, a trouble-shooting report is created. This report is then sent out to service management. Afterwards, the process ends.

description: The process starts when the trouble-shooting report is received by service management. This information goes then into the creation of the problem resolution report. Customer service receives the actual service performance . Subsequently two subsequent activities are triggered. A report is created for the customer which details the current service performance and the resolution of the problem. Secondly, an sla violation rebate is reported to billing & collections who will adjust the billing. Thereafter the report for the customer is sent out to her. After all activities are completed the process ends within customer service. After the customer then receives the report about service performance and problem resolution from customer service, the process flow at the customer also ends.

description: Once the mail centre office of ssp receives an invoice from the client. It categorizes the invoice by staff member. Next the invoice is forwarded to the administration department. Before the department puts all the invoices into a collection box, this department processes the invoice (a complex process). At 10 am every workday, the data entry office takes the invoices and enters all data in the sap system, another complex process. Every hour the mail centre office reviews the system . After the mail centre office forwards all new invoices for validation, the validation office executes the big process of validating invoices. At the beginning of every week, the payment office executes the payment of every validate invoice, this is another big process. After the payment, all invoices are archived by the registry office.

description: A client who wants to create a paypal account first needs to determine the desired account type. He should either select a personal account or a premium account. Next the client should enter login details, such as email address and desired password, personal details, such as name and date of birth, as well as his telephone number and address. Thereafter the client needs to declare if he has been affiliated with any politically exposed person. The client clicks the create account button. The details will be sent to the paypal system. The system will validate the input fields. If any fields are invalid, the client will be notified . Otherwise , a welcome email will be generated and sent to indicate that an account has been created.

In the former case, the offer is forwarded to the financial department and back to the it department. Before the it department prepares an order , the financial department finds resources. description: As soon as an employee files an expense report the process is started. Once the expense report is received a check is performed to make sure the employee has an account. If this check does not take place within 28 days, the process is stopped . In case the employee does not yet have an account, an account is created . Later the report is reviewed. After that, a check is performed to see if the amount of the expense exceeds 200. If it does not exceed 200, the employee is reimbursed through a deposit directly to the bank account of the employee . If it does exceed 200, a supervisor is asked for approval. Three things can happen after this. First, the supervisor approves within 7 days, this will result in the deposit of the reimbursement directly to the bank account of the employee. If the supervisor rejects within 7 days, as a result the employee receives a notification through email that the request has been rejected.

description: In order to apply for admission, students fill in an online form. Online applications are recorded in an information system to which all staff members involved in the admissions process have access to. After that, a student submits the online form. Before the student is requested to download it, a pdf document is generated. After the student must sign it, the student must send it by post together with the required documents. These documents include results of the english language test and curriculum vitae. Before an officer checks the completeness of the documents, these documents are received by the admissions office. If some documents are missing, student has to send the missing documents by post. Assuming the application is complete, the admissions office sends the certified copies of the degrees to an academic recognition agency. After that, the agency checks the degrees . In terms of local education standards, this agency requires that all documents must be certified copies of the originals. In the next step, the agency sends back its assessment to the university by post as well. Assuming the degree verification is successful, the english language test results are then checked online by an officer at the admissions office. If the validity of the english language test results cannot be verified, the process is finished. Once all documents of a given student have been validated, the admission office forwards these documents by internal mail to the corresponding academic committee responsible for deciding whether to offer admission or not. The committee makes its decision based on the academic transcripts and the cv . The committee meets once every 2 to 3 weeks . Afterwards, the committee examines all applications that are ready for academic assessment at the time of the meeting. At the end of the committee meeting, the chair of the committee notifies the admissions office of the selection outcomes. This notification includes a list of admitted and rejected candidates. A few days later, the admission office notifies the outcome to each candidate via email. Additionally, successful candidates are sent a confirmation letter by post.

description: Initially students fill in an online form. Online applications are recorded in an information system to which all staff members involved in the admissions process have access to. Subsequently a student submits the online form. After a pdf document is generated, the student is requested to download it. Before the student must send it by post together with the required documents, the student must sign it. These documents include results of the english language test and curriculum vitae. Before an officer checks the completeness of the documents, these documents are received by the admissions office. If some documents are missing, an email is sent to the student. Assuming the application is complete, the admissions office sends the certified copies of the degrees to an academic recognition agency. Subsequently the agency checks the degrees . In terms of local education standards, this agency requires that all documents be sent to it by post  . Next the agency sends back its assessment to the university by post as well. Assuming the degree verification is successful, the english language test results are then checked online by an officer at the admissions office. If the validity of the english language test results cannot be verified, the process is finished. Once all documents of a given student have been validated, the admission office forwards these documents by internal mail to the corresponding academic committee responsible for deciding whether to offer admission or not. The committee makes its decision based on the academic transcripts and the cv . The committee meets once every 2 to 3 weeks . Afterwards, the committee examines all applications that are ready for academic assessment at the time of the meeting. At the end of the committee meeting, the chair of the committee notifies the admissions office of the selection outcomes. This notification includes a list of admitted and rejected candidates. A few days later, the admission office notifies the outcome to each candidate via email. Additionally, successful candidates are sent a confirmation letter by post.

description: Generally, customers drop their prescriptions in the morning before going to work (or at lunchtime) . Customers drop off their prescriptions either in the drive-through counter or in the front counter of the pharmacy. When dropping their prescription, a technician asks the customer for the pick-up time. In the next step, he puts the prescription in a box labeled with the hour preceding the pick-up time. For example, if the customer asks to have the prescription be ready at 5pm, the technician will drop it in the box with the label 4pm (there is one box for each hour of the day). Every hour, one of the pharmacy technicians picks up the prescriptions due to be filled in the current hour. The technician then enters the details of each prescription (e.g. doctor details, patient details and medication details) into the pharmacy system. Subsequently the pharmacy system performs an automated check called drug utilization review (dur). This check is meant to determine if the prescription contains any drugs that may be incompatible with other drugs that had been dispensed to the same customer in the past, or drugs that may be inappropriate for the customer taking into account the customer data maintained in the system (e.g. age). If any alarms are raised during the automated dur, they are reviewed by a pharmacist who performs a more thorough check. After the dur, the system performs an insurance check in order to determine whether the insurance policy of the customer will pay for part or for the whole cost of the drugs. In most cases, the output of this check is that the insurance company would pay for a certain percentage of the costs, while the customer has to pay for the remaining part (also called the co-payment). The rules for determining how much the insurance company will pay and how much the customer has to pay are very complicated. Every insurance company has different rules. In some cases, the insurance policy does not cover one or several drugs in a prescription, but the drug in question can be replaced by another drug that is covered by the insurance policy, when such cases are detected, the pharmacist generally calls the doctor or the patient to determine if it is possible to perform the drug replacement. If the prescription passes the insurance check, it is assigned to a technician . Before the technician puts them in a bag with the prescription stapled to it, the technician collects the drugs from the shelves . After the technician has filled a given prescription, the bag is passed to the pharmacist who again checks that the prescription has been filled correctly. After this quality check, the pharmacist seals the bag. Before the customer arrives to pick up a prescription, the pharmacist puts it in the pick-up area. Most customers are not willing to wait that long. Thereafter a technician retrieves the prescription . If the drugs in the prescription are not (fully) covered by the insurance of the customer, the technician asks the customer for payment.

description: A purchase request is initiated when an employee at the company fills in a form on paper. The purchase request includes information about the good to be purchased, the quantity, the desired delivery date, the approximate cost. If the employee wants to nominate a specific vendor, the quotes of the vendor are attached to the purchase request. Completing the entire form can take a few days as the requestor often does not have the required data. Afterwards, the employee sends the purchase request through the intranet of the organization . If it is urgent, the employee can hand deliver the form. otherwise , it is circulated via internal mail. More formally, the supervisor has to approve the necessity of the purchase and its conformance with the policy of the company (e.g. does a requested software form part of the standard operating environment?). Collecting the signature from the supervisor takes on average five days. Once a purchase request is approved, it is returned to the employee who initiated the purchase requisition. Later the employee forwards the form to the purchasing department. Afterwards, the central purchasing department checks the completeness of the purchase request . If it is incomplete, a phone call is made to complete the request. Based on attached quotes and other information, the purchasing department enters the approved purchase request into the enterprise system of the company . In case the employee has not nominated any vendors, a clerk at the purchasing Department will select a vendor based either on the quotes attached to the purchase requisition, or based on the list of vendors (also called Master Vendor List) available in the Enterprise System of the company. If the initial quote attached to the request has expired in the meantime, an updated quote is requested from the corresponding vendor. When a vendor is selected, a purchase order is automatically generated by the enterprise system. Afterwards, a fax is sent to the vendor. A copy of the purchase order is sent to accounts payable office, which is part of the financial department. The financial department uses an accounting system that is not integrated with the enterprise system. The goods are always delivered to the goods receipt department. The goods receipt department receives the goods. Subsequently a clerk at this department selects the corresponding purchase order in the enterprise system. Thereafter the clerk checks the quantity and quality of the good. If in the positive case, a document called goods receipt form is generated and stored in the enterprise system. The goods are then forwarded to the employee who initiated the purchase requisition. Then a printout of the goods receipt form is sent to the accounts payable office. If there are any issues with the good, a paper-based note is sent to the purchasing department and to the accounts payable office. The vendor eventually sends the invoice directly to the accounts payable office. Subsequently a clerk at this office compares the purchase order, the goods receipt and the invoice. This task is usually called three-way matching. Three-way matching can be quite time-consuming. If there are any discrepancies such as an error of the vendor or a data entry error, the discrepancies have to be investigated. The duration of the payment process unfortunately takes sometimes so long that the discount for paying in a certain period expires. When a bank transfer is finally triggered , a payment notice is sent to the vendor. Some vendors explicitly indicate in their invoice the bank account number where they want the transfer to occur. It may happen that the bank account number and name indicated in the invoice differs from the one recorded in the vendor database. Sometimes payments bounce back, in which case the vendor is contacted by phone, e-mail or postal mail. Whenever new bank details are given, the transfer is attempted again.

If the initial quote attached to the request has expired in the meantime, an updated quote is requested from the corresponding vendor. When a vendor is selected, a purchase order is automatically generated by the enterprise system. Subsequently a fax is sent to the vendor. A copy of the purchase order is sent to accounts payable office, which is part of the financial department. The financial department uses an accounting system that is not integrated with the enterprise system. The goods are always delivered to the goods receipt department. The goods receipt department receives the goods. Then a clerk at this department selects the corresponding purchase order in the enterprise system. Later the clerk checks the quantity and quality of the good. If in the positive case, a document called goods receipt form is generated and stored in the enterprise system. Whenever there are any issues with the good, a paper-based note is sent to the purchasing department and to the accounts payable office. The vendor eventually sends the invoice directly to the accounts payable office. A clerk at this office compares the purchase order, the goods receipt and the invoice. This task is usually called three-way matching. Three-way matching can be quite time-consuming. Whenever there are any discrepancies such as an error of the vendor or a data entry error, the discrepancies have to be investigated. description: A purchase request is initiated when an employee at the company fills in a form on paper. The purchase request includes information about the good to be purchased, the quantity, the desired delivery date, the approximate cost. If the employee wants to nominate a specific vendor, the quotes of the vendor are attached to the purchase request. Completing the entire form can take a few days as the requestor often does not have the required data. Subsequently the employee sends the purchase request through the intranet of the organization . If it is urgent, the employee can hand deliver the form. otherwise , it is circulated via internal mail. More formally, the supervisor has to provide a financial approval. Collecting the signature from the supervisor takes on average five days. Once a purchase request is approved, it is returned to the employee who initiated the purchase requisition. Next, the employee forwards the form to the purchasing department. Next, the central purchasing department checks the completeness of the purchase request . In case it is incomplete, a phone call is made to complete the request. Based on attached quotes and other information, the purchasing department enters the approved purchase request into the enterprise system of the company . Whenever the employee has not nominated any vendors, a clerk at the purchasing Department will select a vendor based either on the quotes attached to the purchase requisition, or based on the list of vendors (also called Master Vendor List) available in the Enterprise System of the company. If the initial quote attached to the request has expired in the meantime, an updated quote is requested from the corresponding vendor. When a vendor is selected, a purchase order is automatically generated by the enterprise system. In the next step, a fax is sent to the vendor. After that, a copy of the purchase order is sent to accounts payable office, which is part of the financial department. The financial department uses an accounting system that is not integrated with the enterprise system. The goods are always delivered to the goods receipt department. The goods receipt department receives the goods. Then a clerk at this department selects the corresponding purchase order in the enterprise system. Later the clerk checks the quantity and quality of the good. Whenever in the positive case, a document called goods receipt form is generated and stored in the enterprise system. The goods are then forwarded to the employee who initiated the purchase requisition. Thereafter a printout of the goods receipt form is sent to the accounts payable office. If there are any issues with the good, a paper-based note is sent to the purchasing department and to the accounts payable office. The vendor eventually sends the invoice directly to the accounts payable office. Subsequently a clerk at this office compares the purchase order, the goods receipt and the invoice. This task is usually called three-way matching. Three-way matching can be quite time-consuming. Whenever there are any discrepancies such as an error of the vendor or a data entry error, the discrepancies have to be investigated. The duration of the payment process unfortunately takes sometimes so long that the discount for paying in a certain period expires. After a bank transfer is finally triggered , a payment notice is sent to the vendor. Some vendors explicitly indicate in their invoice the bank account number where they want the transfer to occur. It may happen that the bank account number and name indicated in the invoice differs from the one recorded in the vendor database. Sometimes payments bounce back, in which case the vendor is contacted by phone, e-mail or postal mail. In case new bank details are given, the transfer is attempted again.

description: A university provides education and services to its students. First a student sends his admission to the university. When a regular student, i.e. a student who comes from a dutch high-school, sends in his admission form such a student is registered by the admissions office. Then the eligibility to study in a certain program is checked based on the information that the student provided on his admission form. For students who arrive from another school, such as a polytechnic, the previous study that the student took, according to his admission form, must be examined in detail. Students from universities in other countries are also accepted. When students are considered eligible and the courses that they have already followed (if applicable) check out, they are enrolled at the university, which involves sending a letter that they are accepted . Later the details of their enrollment are entered in the information system of the university. The students then become a student of their respective study: industrial engineering, building or construction engineering. After the students are enrolled, they can do projects . Projects are done on an individual basis by a student together with a lecturer. For instance, the lecturer sees the student after work. The university recognizes part-time students who do their studies while they are working in a company. These students typically do projects of a more practical nature than the other students, such that the process that is followed during the project are also different for these students.
solution: <act> register student </act> <act> check eligibility to study in a certain program </act> <path1><act> examine previous study </act></path1>  <act> send letter </act> <act> enter details of their enrollment </act>  <act> do projects </act>

description: A consultancy firm provides consultancy, outsourcing, and interim management services. The firm considers acquisition of projects as part of those services. Acquisition can both be done for existing clients and for new clients, because it concerns acquisition of projects rather than clients. Acquisition is typically started at networking events by partners of the consultancy firm. It is handled according to a fixed procedure, but no standard document is used. When a client shows interest in a consultancy service, an intake is performed with the client. In case the client is new, the firm will always try to establish a framework contract during the intake to maintain a long-term relationship as much as possible. For existing clients, a framework contract does not have to be established.

description: First a process needs to be started by the tribunal in order to hold a hearing . This is done to assess the amount of compensation the tenant owes the owner of the premises. This process starts when a cashier of the tribunal receives a request for compensation from the owner. Next, the cashier retrieves the file for those particular premises . The cashier checks that both the request is acceptable for filing, and compliant with the description of the premises on file. Setting a hearing date incurs fees to the owner. It may be that the owner has already paid the fees with the request, in which case the cashier allocates a hearing date and the process completes. It may be that additional fees are required, but the owner has already paid also those fees, in this case the cashier proceeds with allocating the hearing date.

description: A typical army recruitment process starts by shortlisting all applications of the candidates. Next, those people are then called to sit the following tests: drug and alcohol, eye, color vision, hearing, blood, urine, weight, fingerprinting and doctor examination. The color vision can only be done after the eye test, while the doctor examination can only be done after color vision, hearing, blood, urine and weight have been tested. Moreover, it may be required for some candidates to repeat some of these tests multiple times in order to get a correct assessment. For example the blood test may need to be repeated . In case the candidate has taken too much sugar in the previous 24 hours, the blood test must be performed a second time. Before the candidates are interviewed, the candidates that pass all tests are asked to sit a mental exam and a physical exam. If the candidate passes these two exams and performs well in the interview , the candidate can be recruited in the army.

description: A typical army recruitment process starts by shortlisting all applications of the candidates. Next, those people are then called to sit the following tests: drug and alcohol, eye, color vision, hearing, blood, urine, weight, fingerprinting and doctor examination. The color vision can only be done after the eye test, while the doctor examination can only be done after color vision, hearing, blood, urine and weight have been tested. Moreover, it may be required for some candidates to repeat some of these tests multiple times in order to get a correct assessment. For example the blood test may need to be repeated . If the candidate has taken too much sugar in the previous 24 hours, the blood test must be performed a second time. Before the candidates are interviewed, the candidates that pass all tests are asked to sit a mental exam and a physical exam. If the candidate passes these two exams and performs well in the interview , the candidate can be recruited in the army.

description: A hospital wants to establish a rating workflow for their doctors . To make the workflow reliable, two different roles are assigned. The first one is a referee from the newly created quality assurance department while the second one represents the managing director of the hospital. Both roles execute all of their tasks independently from each other. The referee starts a new case regarding a certain doctor by interviewing patients. Since a patient interview workflow is already established, it is simply integrated in the new workflow. Meanwhile, the director asks an external expert to review the work of the doctor under rating. Unfortunately, since the expert only gets a low expenses fee, it can happen that the expert is not responding in time. In case that happens, another expert has to be asked (who could also not respond in time, i.e. the procedure repeats). If an expert finally sends an expertise, the director forwards the expertise to the referee. Once the referee files the results containing the patient interviews as well as the expertise , the referee creates a report. While the referee is doing this, the manager fills a check to pay the expenses of the expert .

description: In an order management scenario a buyer places an order. Initially a supplier checks the order which contains a list of line item ids and the cumulated price for the items. Once the supplier sends an order response for every line item back to the buyer, the buyer cancels his order . Subsequently the supplier can decide whether the cancellation is valid or not. Therefore, he either acknowledges the cancellation or rejects it. If the order is processed normally , the buyer has to pay the amount he specified in the order.

description: A travel agency wants to establish a booking service. The service is triggered by an incoming request and can return two different messages, either an unavailable notification or a confirmation. The business process of the service starts by first checking the request. If for certain reasons the request can only be handled manually by an employee , a subprocess for manual handling is activated. Otherwise, the process enters a transactional subprocess, where a bus is booked. However, if one of these fails, a log message is written . If both bookings succeed, an attraction is booked by invoking another service. The only thing that could go wrong is a timeout which means. the attraction booking service is not responding in time. If this happens, a manual handling of the booking has to be made. otherwise , a confirmation is sent.
